# meta-rose

Reliable Operating System Enablement (ROSE) Layer provides a basic fail-safe 
image configuration which could be used for embedded systems.

Dependencies
============

This layer depends on:

  URI: git://git.yoctoproject.org/poky.git
  layers: meta meta-yocto
  branch: daisy


Table of Contents
=================

  I. Adding the rose layer to your build
 II. Misc

I. Adding the rose layer to your build
=================================================

In order to use this layer, you need to make the build system aware of
it.

Assuming the rose layer exists at the top-level of your
yocto build tree, you can add it to the build system by adding the
location of the rose layer to bblayers.conf, along with any
other layers needed. e.g.:

  BBLAYERS ?= " \
    /path/to/yocto/meta \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto-bsp \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-rose \
    "


